      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1783693115530,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Coupling is the \"killer\" - causes almost all of our problems.\n    - coupling is the strength of relationships between code \"thingies\" (classes, methods, etc.)\n    - If you change something in one place, is it going to break somewhere else? That is coupling.\n    - Our unit test was trying to tell us that we had coupling between the concept of bonus calculation and\n      account management.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Coupling is the \"killer\" - causes almost all of our problems.\n    - coupling is the strength of relationships between code \"thingies\" (classes, methods, etc.)\n    - If you change something in one place, is it going to break somewhere else? That is coupling.\n    - Our unit test was trying to tell us that we had coupling between the concept of bonus calculation and\n      account management.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
